import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Miles_per_Gallon'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Miles_per_Gallon')
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Miles_per_Gallon')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Miles_per_Gallon?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['Cylinders'], data['Miles_per_Gallon'], c=data['Cylinders'], cmap='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Cylinders')
    plt.ylabel('Miles_per_Gallon')
    plt.title('How does the Miles_per_Gallon vary with the number of Cylinders?', wrap=True)
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Cylinders")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
